Oh, very bad move.  Must keep an eye out for those pesky rook/king and (even worse) queen/king forks.  Ne2+ gives up the queen for free.  Qg5 sets the queen up for QxPg7#, if black moves the knight.  But black would probably still go for Ne2+, followed by NxBc3.  Qh5 wouldn't protect against Ne2+ because black's e rook is defending that square.
